column5: I just want to comment on how great the reports have been lately. I haven't seen this many nice weather/nice fish/family reports in a long time! The Musky reports have been especially epic lately! I'm looking forward to the fall BOQ and other walleye factory (Musky Mike, Limeyangler and others) reports.  OFC is pure gold sometimes; the past few days have proven that!!
yup nice to have some good reports/discussions before the inevitable period of "cabin fever" sets in and we all look at each other kinda funny
Well thank you for noticing.  That's the way it's always worked here. Group hug!

Don't forget all the informative discussions on tackle and eqipment Alot of the great info from these threads is helping me to plan my future equipment purchases for next season.What i find really unique here is the mixture of sincerity, sillyness,experience and knowledge. I have yet to see its equal,anywhere else on the web. A big manly hug to all of you.
What ta hec is going on in here ......lol .
Sorry I forgot to mention all the great "perch in pocket" reports.
You didn't know? Skippy's last name is Popeil. The original pocket fisherman.
Hey ! thanks RC...lol. It is the best i agree , so much coming at you , its hard to take it all in .
Roy you must be in cahutz with La La ... lol
Dont forget about the deer and moose and fall turkey hunt,some quackers and late season river reports, and then it will be the ice reports. Im not seeing any cabin fever in my near future.
and this is where I chime in and kill the thread....  sorry guys/gals.  Awesome info/personalities on this site, for sure
